Sarah, I wanna start this with a little tiny story,

15
00:00:49.467 --> 00:00:51.702
just to kind of set it up because it happened

16
00:00:51.702 --> 00:00:53.071
in the last 24 hours.

17
00:00:53.071 --> 00:00:55.840
So here we are in Sedona, my heart's home,

18
00:00:55.840 --> 00:00:58.876
your home as well, and I thought, "While in Rome,"

19
00:00:58.876 --> 00:01:02.014
and I was pondering something and I was at a friend's house

20
00:01:02.014 --> 00:01:04.116
who had a number of sets of little cards, you know,

21
00:01:04.116 --> 00:01:06.484
the divination cards, angel cards and such.

22
00:01:06.484 --> 00:01:07.886
I thought, "Sure, why not?"

23
00:01:07.886 --> 00:01:09.420
picked a deck, rolled it out,

24
00:01:09.420 --> 00:01:11.790
and I was asking about something very deep and profound,

25
00:01:11.790 --> 00:01:14.460
and it said, "Listen," right?

26
00:01:14.460 --> 00:01:15.193
<v ->Mm-hmm.</v>

27
00:01:15.193 --> 00:01:16.728
<v Regina>And about going inside</v>

28
00:01:16.728 --> 00:01:20.681
and getting the deeper messages, to be quiet.

29
00:01:21.499 --> 00:01:23.235
My host, the friend, said,

30
00:01:23.235 --> 00:01:25.577
"I chose those exact two cards earlier this morning."

31
00:01:25.577 --> 00:01:26.404
<v ->Oh. (laughs)</v>

32
00:01:26.404 --> 00:01:28.807
In two different decks, she chose "Listen."

33
00:01:28.807 --> 00:01:31.643
I told my other friend, the one I'm staying with,

34
00:01:31.643 --> 00:01:33.043
and she said, "That's so funny,

35
00:01:33.043 --> 00:01:34.213
"I just had the same conversation

36
00:01:34.213 --> 00:01:35.814
"with my son this morning."

37
00:01:35.814 --> 00:01:39.685
So en masse, there's this imperative

38
00:01:39.685 --> 00:01:40.986
that we begin listening,

39
00:01:40.986 --> 00:01:43.288
and I'm sure for very practical reasons

40
00:01:43.288 --> 00:01:45.890
as well as deep spiritual reasons.

41
00:01:45.890 --> 00:01:46.758
<v ->Mm-hmm.</v>

42
00:01:46.758 --> 00:01:49.160
<v Regina>And that's what so lovely about what you do,</v>

43
00:01:49.160 --> 00:01:52.630
is because your passion, your mission in life

44
00:01:52.630 --> 00:01:55.634
is to help anybody start listening

45
00:01:55.634 --> 00:01:58.903
to their own true voice via meditation,

46
00:01:58.903 --> 00:02:00.162
<v ->Yes.
<v Regina>And you're just</v>

47
00:02:00.162 --> 00:02:01.338
superb at what you do.

48
00:02:01.338 --> 00:02:04.075
You get through to the rich and the famous

49
00:02:04.075 --> 00:02:08.179
as well as people in the judicial system,

50
00:02:08.179 --> 00:02:10.281
justices, so forth, everybody.

51
00:02:10.281 --> 00:02:11.249
<v ->Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.</v>

52
00:02:11.249 --> 00:02:12.551
<v Regina>So let's talk about how that happened to you,</v>

53
00:02:12.551 --> 00:02:14.653
because you're a wild adventurer.

54
00:02:14.653 --> 00:02:15.721
You've been in the Army,

55
00:02:15.721 --> 00:02:18.223
you've traveled around the world on a bicycle.

56
00:02:18.223 --> 00:02:19.524
(both laugh)

57
00:02:19.524 --> 00:02:22.594
I mean you've lived in countries all over.

58
00:02:22.594 --> 00:02:23.395
You've done it all.

59
00:02:23.395 --> 00:02:24.502
You've lived in ashrams.

60
00:02:24.502 --> 00:02:25.597
<v ->Mm-hmm.
<v Regina>So tell us about</v>

61
00:02:25.597 --> 00:02:27.665
how this began for you.

62
00:02:27.665 --> 00:02:29.967
<v ->I think it had to do with listening really.</v>

63
00:02:29.967 --> 00:02:33.137
I really do because I was about 26 years old,

64
00:02:33.137 --> 00:02:36.408
and I had what most people are searching for,

65
00:02:36.408 --> 00:02:38.010
a really beautiful home,

66
00:02:38.010 --> 00:02:40.445
I had a great job, I was making great money,

67
00:02:40.445 --> 00:02:42.447
and I had a wonderful partner,

68
00:02:42.447 --> 00:02:45.016
and I was healthy and happy.

69
00:02:45.016 --> 00:02:47.719
And one day, I looked around and I thought,

70
00:02:47.719 --> 00:02:49.454
"Is that all there is?"

71
00:02:49.454 --> 00:02:52.790
And I was attracted to reading a book review,

72
00:02:52.790 --> 00:02:56.895
and I remember reading about this approach to healing

73
00:02:56.895 --> 00:03:00.132
by an Indian man who was writing a book about it,

74
00:03:00.132 --> 00:03:03.635
and I was reading about how he used herbs and diet

75
00:03:03.635 --> 00:03:06.804
and daily routine and meditation and massage,

76
00:03:06.804 --> 00:03:09.141
and I thought, "Oh, that sounds interesting."

77
00:03:09.141 --> 00:03:10.342
In the Army, I was a medic,

78
00:03:10.342 --> 00:03:14.279
and we really treated the body more like a machine.

79
00:03:14.279 --> 00:03:18.416
But here was this man who was sort of bringing to light

80
00:03:18.416 --> 00:03:22.153
how all of these approaches through the senses

81
00:03:22.153 --> 00:03:23.888
could bring about balance.

82
00:03:23.888 --> 00:03:25.724
And I went and picked up that book,

83
00:03:25.724 --> 00:03:28.793
and it was called Perfect Health by Deepak Chopra,

84
00:03:28.793 --> 00:03:31.195
who, at the time, was not a household name.

85
00:03:31.195 --> 00:03:34.232
And so I immediately read that book and said

86
00:03:34.232 --> 00:03:36.735
I want everything in this book.

87
00:03:36.735 --> 00:03:39.037
I wanna know how to practice

88
00:03:39.037 --> 00:03:41.339
everything this man is talking about.

89
00:03:41.339 --> 00:03:44.743
And it became about the science of Ayurveda.

90
00:03:44.743 --> 00:03:47.913
Ayur means life, and veda means knowledge,

91
00:03:47.913 --> 00:03:50.482
so it's the knowledge of life and longevity.

92
00:03:50.482 --> 00:03:53.151
And so I immediately picked up the phone

93
00:03:53.151 --> 00:03:56.026
and called and said, "Can I work for you?"

94
00:03:56.026 --> 00:03:58.390
And they said, "Sure, come on down.

95
00:03:58.390 --> 00:04:00.592
"You can volunteer and answer the phones."

96
00:04:00.592 --> 00:04:02.927
And actually, it was in Massachusetts where I had grown up,

97
00:04:02.927 --> 00:04:04.730
so I was pretty fearless on that.

98
00:04:04.730 --> 00:04:08.833
I left my entire life and I went to Massachusetts

99
00:04:08.833 --> 00:04:12.871
and worked as a volunteer, living in an environment

100
00:04:12.871 --> 00:04:15.507
with a whole bunch of other people who meditated

101
00:04:15.507 --> 00:04:17.575
and practiced Ayurveda.

102
00:04:17.575 --> 00:04:20.044
And I got very involved in meditation

103
00:04:20.044 --> 00:04:22.681
because that was the primary approach

104
00:04:22.681 --> 00:04:25.383
for reducing stress in the nervous system

105
00:04:25.383 --> 00:04:29.454
and for pretty much getting in touch with who we are

106
00:04:29.454 --> 00:04:32.423
outside of illness or disease

107
00:04:32.423 --> 00:04:35.260
or outside of who we think we are,

108
00:04:35.260 --> 00:04:36.961
outside of the roles we play

109
00:04:36.961 --> 00:04:38.997
and the responsibilities we have.

110
00:04:38.997 --> 00:04:40.264
So it was really a...

111
00:04:40.264 --> 00:04:42.133
It was the primary approach to healing,

112
00:04:42.133 --> 00:04:43.501
and I didn't realize it at the time

113
00:04:43.501 --> 00:04:45.137
I was reading that book review,

114
00:04:45.137 --> 00:04:47.172
but the word Ayurveda,

115
00:04:47.172 --> 00:04:49.040
I remember talking with someone

116
00:04:49.040 --> 00:04:50.942
right after I had read this book review,

117
00:04:50.942 --> 00:04:53.245
and I said, "That's what I'm going to be doing."

118
00:04:53.245 --> 00:04:55.747
It was like a listening, like, "That's it."

119
00:04:55.747 --> 00:04:57.982
And so you talk about listening,

120
00:04:57.982 --> 00:05:01.286
and it brings up what I've heard

121
00:05:01.286 --> 00:05:03.154
a lot of people talk about here in Sedona.

122
00:05:03.154 --> 00:05:06.091
They say, "Prayer is talking to God,

123
00:05:06.091 --> 00:05:08.727
"and meditation is listening to God."

124
00:05:08.727 --> 00:05:10.295
<v Regina>That's a very good way to say it.</v>

125
00:05:10.295 --> 00:05:13.665
<v ->It is, but I've really thought about it like a koan,</v>

126
00:05:13.665 --> 00:05:16.301
and I thought prayer is talking to God

127
00:05:16.301 --> 00:05:17.736
and sometimes listening.

128
00:05:17.736 --> 00:05:19.071
<v Regina>Or asking a lot of,</v>

129
00:05:19.071 --> 00:05:20.939
asking for a lot of favors.

130
00:05:20.939 --> 00:05:22.973
<v ->Yeah (laughs), right.
(Regina laughs)

131
00:05:22.973 --> 00:05:24.209
"Please, please, please!"

132
00:05:24.209 --> 00:05:25.644
<v Regina>"Please, I'll do this if you'll do that."</v>

133
00:05:25.644 --> 00:05:26.911
<v ->Right (laughs).</v>

134
00:05:26.911 --> 00:05:30.048
But then when I really looked at it more deeply,

135
00:05:30.048 --> 00:05:33.552
is I realized that meditation helps us,

136
00:05:33.552 --> 00:05:35.019
it's like the big Q-tip,

137
00:05:35.019 --> 00:05:37.889
helps us to almost purify our senses

138
00:05:37.889 --> 00:05:40.859
so we can more clearly listen

139
00:05:40.859 --> 00:05:43.978
and pay attention to the whispers.

140
00:05:43.978 --> 00:05:47.499
<v Regina>Absolutely, and this is a really key point.</v>

141
00:05:47.499 --> 00:05:52.470
Right now, we're living in an age of disinformation,

142
00:05:52.470 --> 00:05:56.941
saturation of information until our minds and our bodies

143
00:05:56.941 --> 00:05:59.210
are on complete overload.

144
00:05:59.210 --> 00:06:00.779
And not only that, it's becoming...

145
00:06:00.779 --> 00:06:03.114
There are so many voices saying so many things,

146
00:06:03.114 --> 00:06:05.684
with the explosion in access through YouTube,

147
00:06:05.684 --> 00:06:07.719
the Internet, and so forth

148
00:06:07.719 --> 00:06:10.988
that we hear from a lot of our viewers,

149
00:06:10.988 --> 00:06:13.959
"I am so overloaded, I don't know where to even begin now."

150
00:06:13.959 --> 00:06:14.926
<v ->Right.</v>

151
00:06:14.926 --> 00:06:19.926
<v Regina>And the only place we really have to go</v>

152
00:06:19.931 --> 00:06:24.469
is inside to hear our own refined voice,

153
00:06:24.469 --> 00:06:27.038
the highest essence of ourselves.

154
00:06:27.038 --> 00:06:30.474
And you can't do that without being still.

155
00:06:30.474 --> 00:06:33.944
You can't do that without some form of meditative practice,

156
00:06:33.944 --> 00:06:36.881
and I would guess every person listening to this right now

157
00:06:36.881 --> 00:06:40.388
would love to have full access to themselves

158
00:06:40.388 --> 00:06:42.820
to find out what is it, for them and their lives,

159
00:06:42.820 --> 00:06:45.323
absolutely their truth.

160
00:06:45.323 --> 00:06:46.224
<v ->Yes.
<v Regina>And it might not be</v>

161
00:06:46.224 --> 00:06:48.493
someone else's truth but their truth.

162
00:06:48.493 --> 00:06:50.495
Only you can give your truth, right?

163
00:06:50.495 --> 00:06:51.996
<v ->Right, and I love...</v>

164
00:06:51.996 --> 00:06:54.700
That is one of the biggest benefits of meditation.

165
00:06:54.700 --> 00:06:57.101
Sure, it's been researched so much now

166
00:06:57.101 --> 00:06:58.936
and all the clinics are recommending it,

167
00:06:58.936 --> 00:07:02.841
Mayo Clinic and Harvard Center for Mind-Body Healing,

168
00:07:02.841 --> 00:07:05.844
but more than lowering blood pressure

169
00:07:05.844 --> 00:07:08.480
and enhancing the immune system

170
00:07:08.480 --> 00:07:12.617
and relieving the stress in the cardiovascular system,

171
00:07:12.617 --> 00:07:14.619
the side effect or the side benefit

172
00:07:14.619 --> 00:07:16.921
that I most love about meditation

173
00:07:16.921 --> 00:07:20.558
is that it slowly and subtly

174
00:07:20.558 --> 00:07:23.762
moves the reference point in our lives

175
00:07:23.762 --> 00:07:26.597
from the world out there of noise and phenomenon

176
00:07:26.597 --> 00:07:30.635
and information and what other people's opinions are of us,

177
00:07:30.635 --> 00:07:34.638
subtly, we start to become our own authority.

178
00:07:34.638 --> 00:07:38.810
We start to become, as Deepak Chopra would say,

179
00:07:38.810 --> 00:07:41.446
we start to become "self-referred,"

180
00:07:41.446 --> 00:07:45.218
referring really as our inner wisdom

181
00:07:45.218 --> 00:07:47.085
becomes our reference point.

182
00:07:47.085 --> 00:07:49.187
So no matter what's happening out there,

183
00:07:49.187 --> 00:07:52.690
whether it be bad weather or even a natural disaster

184
00:07:52.690 --> 00:07:57.690
or losing a job or getting into an argument with a partner,

185
00:07:57.863 --> 00:08:02.400
it's almost like that's happening, yes, that's the scenery,

186
00:08:02.400 --> 00:08:06.104
but the one who is experiencing it is so rooted

187
00:08:06.104 --> 00:08:10.241
in balance and presence that it doesn't ever

188
00:08:10.241 --> 00:08:13.344
get overshadowed by the world out there.

189
00:08:13.344 --> 00:08:16.314
And I think that is what the real issues are.

190
00:08:16.314 --> 00:08:19.317
And I say surround yourself in silence.

191
00:08:19.317 --> 00:08:21.887
Really take a look at

192
00:08:21.887 --> 00:08:24.223
what you are putting in your environment,

193
00:08:24.223 --> 00:08:27.225
the noises that you...

194
00:08:27.225 --> 00:08:29.327
are out there and that are coming in.

195
00:08:29.327 --> 00:08:32.029
Do you walk into your apartment and flip on the television

196
00:08:32.029 --> 00:08:34.266
or automatically turn on the radio

197
00:08:34.266 --> 00:08:36.868
or automatically get on the phone

198
00:08:36.868 --> 00:08:39.338
just to fill up that silence?

199
00:08:39.338 --> 00:08:40.371
It's almost like we need to give

200
00:08:40.371 --> 00:08:42.173
our nervous systems a break.

201
00:08:42.173 --> 00:08:43.007
<v Regina>Hugely.</v>

202
00:08:43.007 --> 00:08:43.741
<v ->Yeah.</v>

203
00:08:43.741 --> 00:08:45.210
<v Regina>And let's talk about some of...</v>

204
00:08:45.210 --> 00:08:49.448
Because you see the entire swath of society, everyone,

205
00:08:49.448 --> 00:08:53.486
what are you seeing by way of this incredible interference

206
00:08:53.486 --> 00:08:56.121
with the nervous system, the mind, and so forth?

207
00:08:56.121 --> 00:08:58.923
Can you give us just a couple of anecdotal situations

208
00:08:58.923 --> 00:09:02.427
of people who have sought you out or found their way to you

209
00:09:02.427 --> 00:09:06.564
who are literally shattered with so much incoming

210
00:09:06.564 --> 00:09:09.568
they couldn't handle it any more?

211
00:09:09.568 --> 00:09:12.037
<v ->Well, I have people coming to learn to meditate</v>

212
00:09:12.037 --> 00:09:15.873
from all walks of life, whether it be they've just,

213
00:09:15.873 --> 00:09:17.108
their partner just died

214
00:09:17.108 --> 00:09:19.412
or they found out they're at stage four in cancer

215
00:09:19.412 --> 00:09:21.212
or they've lost their job

216
00:09:21.212 --> 00:09:23.548
or they've retired and they don't know who they are

217
00:09:23.548 --> 00:09:25.484
without their reference point of the work.

218
00:09:25.484 --> 00:09:26.550
<v Regina>Without the business card.</v>

219
00:09:26.550 --> 00:09:27.585
<v ->Right.</v>

220
00:09:27.585 --> 00:09:30.622
So I work with many people on that level,

221
00:09:30.622 --> 00:09:33.625
and it's almost like their dark night of the soul.

222
00:09:33.625 --> 00:09:37.329
And I had mine, and it was a couple of days, I mean,

223
00:09:37.329 --> 00:09:41.600
and this is the fallacy that there is only one in your life

224
00:09:41.600 --> 00:09:44.069
(laughs) because there can be a few.

225
00:09:44.069 --> 00:09:47.005
But I often am with people while they're

226
00:09:47.005 --> 00:09:48.240
in the middle of that

227
00:09:48.240 --> 00:09:50.240
or in the middle of their wake-up call.

228
00:09:50.240 --> 00:09:51.909
And of course, it'd be great to avoid that

229
00:09:51.909 --> 00:09:54.313
and wake up before the wake-up call.

230
00:09:54.313 --> 00:09:57.949
But I find that people have...

231
00:09:57.949 --> 00:10:00.285
I think that stress is building up in the nervous system,

232
00:10:00.285 --> 00:10:03.221
whether it be from external too much noise

233
00:10:03.221 --> 00:10:06.125
or toxicity in the environment or the food

234
00:10:06.125 --> 00:10:08.826
or toxic relationships, whether it to be a job

235
00:10:08.826 --> 00:10:13.665
or to a spouse or to friends or to family members.

236
00:10:13.665 --> 00:10:17.936
I find that this layer of stress keeps us

237
00:10:17.936 --> 00:10:21.406
from really acknowledging our inner wisdom.

238
00:10:21.406 --> 00:10:23.475
So for instance, a woman came to me,

239
00:10:23.475 --> 00:10:25.577
and she was with her husband who had had a stroke.

240
00:10:25.577 --> 00:10:27.579
They were visiting from Detroit.

241
00:10:27.579 --> 00:10:29.514
They lived in a very,

242
00:10:29.514 --> 00:10:31.315
not a great neighborhood.

243
00:10:31.315 --> 00:10:34.986
She had just retired from being a school teacher.

244
00:10:34.986 --> 00:10:36.788
She was there for years.

245
00:10:36.788 --> 00:10:40.059
And often, when people come to meditate with me,

246
00:10:40.059 --> 00:10:42.660
I ask them, "Well, what do you want?

247
00:10:42.660 --> 00:10:44.161
"What do you really want?"

248
00:10:44.161 --> 00:10:46.932
Most people haven't even asked themselves that question.

249
00:10:46.932 --> 00:10:49.467
And I said, "Well, if you dare to dream,

250
00:10:49.467 --> 00:10:50.068
"what would you want?"

251
00:10:50.068 --> 00:10:52.304
She goes, "I I want to live in Sedona."

252
00:10:52.304 --> 00:10:55.974
And I said, "Well, why wouldn't you be able to do that?"

253
00:10:55.974 --> 00:10:57.442
She said, "Well, I can't sell my house.

254
00:10:57.442 --> 00:10:58.610
"It's not worth anything.

255
00:10:58.610 --> 00:11:00.812
"We owe more than what its value is,

