00:30:38.445 --> 00:30:40.391
Obviously, you can't do it while you're driving,

774
00:30:40.391 --> 00:30:41.860
but park down the street,

775
00:30:41.860 --> 00:30:44.132
close your eyes, lock the door,

776
00:30:44.132 --> 00:30:45.164
time yourself.

777
00:30:45.164 --> 00:30:47.031
Just it's your sanctuary.

778
00:30:47.031 --> 00:30:48.666
Turn the music off though.

779
00:30:48.666 --> 00:30:52.403
Anything that starts to attract your attention outward

780
00:30:52.403 --> 00:30:54.873
is sort of going against what we're trying to do,

781
00:30:54.873 --> 00:30:57.009
which is turning the attention inward.

782
00:30:57.009 --> 00:30:59.610
So closing the eyes, timing it.

783
00:30:59.610 --> 00:31:01.913
I'm in this grocery store parking lot

784
00:31:01.913 --> 00:31:03.749
all the time between appointments.

785
00:31:03.749 --> 00:31:06.684
And ideally, meditate before you eat

786
00:31:06.684 --> 00:31:08.687
because when you eat, the body is really working

787
00:31:08.687 --> 00:31:11.089
to take the world out there

788
00:31:11.089 --> 00:31:13.925
and turn it into the world that we call your body

789
00:31:13.925 --> 00:31:16.561
through food and the digestion process.

790
00:31:16.561 --> 00:31:19.631
So when we meditate, the body starts slowing down,

791
00:31:19.631 --> 00:31:21.999
and when we're eating, it starts to speed up.

792
00:31:21.999 --> 00:31:24.135
So we want to do it after we eat,

793
00:31:24.135 --> 00:31:26.237
at least after an hour after we eat,

794
00:31:26.237 --> 00:31:28.140
or before we eat.

795
00:31:28.140 --> 00:31:30.076
<v Regina>Let's talk about insomniacs</v>

796
00:31:30.076 --> 00:31:33.444
because I mean this does affect sleep patterns,

797
00:31:33.444 --> 00:31:36.549
but I personally, I like it when I wake up,

798
00:31:36.549 --> 00:31:38.416
if something wakes me up at 3 or 4 in the morning.

799
00:31:38.416 --> 00:31:40.085
That's a beautiful time, I find,

800
00:31:40.085 --> 00:31:41.553
the clearest time to meditate.

801
00:31:41.553 --> 00:31:45.256
There's not a lot of any kind of noise of any kind,

802
00:31:45.256 --> 00:31:47.759
physical, psychic noise, you name it.

803
00:31:47.759 --> 00:31:52.064
But what about using this for sleep disturbances

804
00:31:52.064 --> 00:31:52.830
or sleep patterns?

805
00:31:52.830 --> 00:31:53.832
<v Sarah>That's a great question.</v>

806
00:31:53.832 --> 00:31:56.535
Well, one of the things, I've read a lot of research,

807
00:31:56.535 --> 00:31:58.971
and a lot of the research proves

808
00:31:58.971 --> 00:32:02.373
that meditation helps to reduce sleeping medication,

809
00:32:02.373 --> 00:32:04.443
helps to improve the quality of sleep,

810
00:32:04.443 --> 00:32:07.913
and sleep is the number one way we get rid of stress

811
00:32:07.913 --> 00:32:09.046
in our nervous system.

812
00:32:09.046 --> 00:32:10.748
So when we have so much stress

813
00:32:10.748 --> 00:32:13.150
that it starts to affect the quality of our sleep,

814
00:32:13.150 --> 00:32:14.952
really, it's a double whammy.

815
00:32:14.952 --> 00:32:17.055
We are not able to recover quickly.

816
00:32:17.055 --> 00:32:19.724
So yes, meditation has been proven

817
00:32:19.724 --> 00:32:21.760
to increase the quality of sleep.

818
00:32:21.760 --> 00:32:24.696
Now I wanna just explain this because,

819
00:32:24.696 --> 00:32:27.265
because sometimes, when we finish meditating,

820
00:32:27.265 --> 00:32:28.600
we feel really relaxed.

821
00:32:28.600 --> 00:32:30.769
It feels like, "Oh, I could go right to sleep."

822
00:32:30.769 --> 00:32:34.873
But over time, you're going to really feel clearer.

823
00:32:34.873 --> 00:32:36.330
It's sort of this clear awareness.

824
00:32:36.330 --> 00:32:37.145
<v Regina>Right.</v>

825
00:32:37.145 --> 00:32:40.212
<v ->So ideally, you don't meditate right before bed.</v>

826
00:32:40.212 --> 00:32:43.248
You meditate before, ideally before breakfast

827
00:32:43.248 --> 00:32:45.017
and then again before dinner.

828
00:32:45.017 --> 00:32:47.919
If you can't do one of those, you can do it before lunch.

829
00:32:47.919 --> 00:32:50.255
But you've mentioned the yogic hour.

830
00:32:50.255 --> 00:32:52.691
There is this hour between 4 and 6 am,

831
00:32:52.691 --> 00:32:54.425
before sunrise.
<v Regina>Mm, it's wonderful.</v>

832
00:32:54.425 --> 00:32:56.094
<v ->It's traditional for meditation.</v>

833
00:32:56.094 --> 00:32:57.829
That's the ambrosia hour.

834
00:32:57.829 --> 00:33:00.264
And when I lived in a Zen Buddhist monastery,

835
00:33:00.264 --> 00:33:02.500
we would be awake at that time

836
00:33:02.500 --> 00:33:05.370
and we would start our first meditation before 5.

837
00:33:05.370 --> 00:33:08.506
And that is the time where the nervous system

838
00:33:08.506 --> 00:33:10.975
has gotten its deep rest from sleep

839
00:33:10.975 --> 00:33:13.912
so that you're not dealing with the big stresses

840
00:33:13.912 --> 00:33:16.381
but you're actually able to refine

841
00:33:16.381 --> 00:33:20.251
some of the other stresses that might get in the way

842
00:33:20.251 --> 00:33:21.653
of you listening to you.

843
00:33:21.653 --> 00:33:23.923
<v Regina>Mm-hmm, it's a lovely experience.</v>

844
00:33:23.923 --> 00:33:24.823
<v ->It is.</v>

845
00:33:24.823 --> 00:33:26.358
<v Regina>It's my favorite (laughs).</v>

846
00:33:26.358 --> 00:33:28.559
I mean when you're in there, in that state,

