00:34:06.964 --> 00:34:09.247
are doing things we don't really like that we're doing,

867
00:34:09.247 --> 00:34:11.670
and it's again the habit of mind.

868
00:34:11.670 --> 00:34:13.805
And I think meditation really helps us

869
00:34:13.805 --> 00:34:18.142
to focus on who we really are outside of

870
00:34:18.142 --> 00:34:21.680
whether it's a sickness or our jobs or our family,

871
00:34:21.680 --> 00:34:24.984
who we really are and what we really want.

872
00:34:24.984 --> 00:34:27.619
I was always afraid to ask for what I wanted

873
00:34:27.619 --> 00:34:29.588
because I didn't even know what it was.

874
00:34:29.588 --> 00:34:31.756
And I had voices in my head from family members

875
00:34:31.756 --> 00:34:34.460
who would say, "Can't you stop being so selfish?"

876
00:34:34.460 --> 00:34:36.928
or, "I wouldn't do that if I were you,"

877
00:34:36.928 --> 00:34:39.831
or that kind of thing which sort of thwarted

878
00:34:39.831 --> 00:34:42.266
my own conversation with myself.

879
00:34:42.266 --> 00:34:44.836
And I think meditation helps us to reconnect

880
00:34:44.836 --> 00:34:47.138
with what we really want,

881
00:34:47.138 --> 00:34:49.474
what really makes our soul sing,

882
00:34:49.474 --> 00:34:52.767
and that's the real reason that we're here.

883
00:34:52.767 --> 00:34:55.480
We each need to sing our song, really,

884
00:34:55.480 --> 00:34:57.349
and I'm not trying to be esoteric.

885
00:34:57.349 --> 00:34:59.485
It's how can we do that

886
00:34:59.485 --> 00:35:01.286
without taking somebody else's idea

887
00:35:01.286 --> 00:35:04.055
of what that looks like and imposing it on ourselves.

888
00:35:04.055 --> 00:35:06.425
So meditation helps us to get clear about that.

889
00:35:06.425 --> 00:35:08.560
<v Regina>Absolutely, and break out of the prison</v>

890
00:35:08.560 --> 00:35:11.596
